			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-369696">
				April 4, 2015 at 16:01					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>No, I&#8217;m saying that one side has dominated the publishing houses, and one side had dominated the elected nominees for around two decades now.  If the others here are gonna resort to hyperbole, then I can too.  I&#8217;d rather not.</p>
<p>The Hugo&#8217;s have had an influx of interest, an influx of fans like they haven&#8217;t seen in years, and one side doesn&#8217;t want those fans to come in because it&#8217;s &#8220;Political&#8221;.  The selection  was all across the board. And if it was weighted to the brash newcomers side this once, out of nearly two decades&#8230;well, sometimes it takes a stick of dynamite to blast a stump out of a hole.</p>
</div>

				<div class="reply">
				<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?replytocom=369696#respond' data-commentid="369696" data-postid="2177" data-belowelement="comment-369696" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label='Reply to Rick Bennett'>Reply</a>				</div><!-- .reply -->
